comment: Constants used by Chrome in SPNEGO authentication requests to the Android Account Manager.

variables.name: KEY_INCOMING_AUTH_TOKEN
variables.comment: The token provided by in the HTTP 401 response (Base64 encoded string)

variables.name: KEY_SPNEGO_CONTEXT
variables.comment: The SPNEGO Context from the previous transaction (Bundle) - also used in the response bundle

variables.name: KEY_SPNEGO_RESULT
variables.comment: The returned status from the authenticator.

variables.name: SPNEGO_TOKEN_TYPE_BASE
variables.comment: Prefix of token type. Full token type is "SPNEGO:HOSTBASED:<spn>"

variables.name: OK
variables.comment: All OK. Returned token is valid.

variables.name: ERR_UNEXPECTED
variables.comment: An unexpected error. This may be caused by a programming mistake or an invalid assumption.

variables.name: ERR_ABORTED
variables.comment: Request aborted due to user action.

variables.name: ERR_UNEXPECTED_SECURITY_LIBRARY_STATUS
variables.comment: An unexpected, but documented, SSPI or GSSAPI status code was returned.

variables.name: ERR_INVALID_AUTH_CREDENTIALS
variables.comment: Credentials could not be established during HTTP Authentication.

variables.name: ERR_UNSUPPORTED_AUTH_SCHEME
variables.comment: An HTTP Authentication scheme was tried which is not supported on this machine.

variables.name: ERR_MISSING_AUTH_CREDENTIALS
variables.comment: (GSSAPI) No Kerberos credentials were available during HTTP Authentication.

variables.name: ERR_UNDOCUMENTED_SECURITY_LIBRARY_STATUS
variables.comment: An undocumented SSPI or GSSAPI status code was returned.

variables.name: ERR_MALFORMED_IDENTITY
variables.comment: The identity used for authentication is invalid.
